title: Bug 109350: Output parameter should display in data set dialog.
OB: When calling the stored procedure from Oracle database, the query result has been stored in an output parameter as an object. However, in the query result page, no data is returned.
EB: The output parameter should display in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
To reproduce:
1. Call the stored procedure from Oracle database.
2. Check if the query result is stored in the output parameter.
3. Open the edit data set dialog and verify if the output parameter is displayed.
